2. In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires- Interpretation
"additional assets" means any tangible assets, excluding land, that belong to a
farmer, trader or related business, pertaining directly or indirectly to
agricultural production, processing or trade, all accounts receivable, chattel
paper, warehouse receipts, both negotiable and non-negotiable, promissory
notes and includes savings accounts on deposit with any bank, credit union,
savings institution or other similar organisation;
